17/05/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The US Air Force will hold a joint exercise in Bulgaria next month, the defence ministry announced on Tuesday (16 May). 
The event will take place at the Graf Ignatievo air base in central Bulgaria.
In other news, Bulgaria has lifted a ban on the sale of live poultry in open markets. 
Authorities have decided that the threat of migratory birds spreading avian flu has now subsided, though neighbouring Romania is detecting new cases. 
(Reuters, AP - 16/05/06)
